1/4 cup Primal Kitchen Garlic Aioli Mayo
4 strips of bacon (cooked) 
4 slices turkey

2 heads iceberg lettuce (cored and outside leaves removed)

Looking for a new sweet and salty side dish to serve in your Turkey Day spread? Use Primal Kitchen Snickerdoodle Collagen Fuel® and Avocado Oil to make this deceptively decadent Sweet Potato Casserole, topped with Spiced Pecans. 🤤
.
Ingredients:
For the sweet potatoes:
5 lbs. sweet potatoes
2 eggs
1/4 cup coconut sugar
2 scoops Primal Kitchen Collagen Fuel (Vanilla or Snickerdoodle)
1 tsp. cinnamon (if not using Snickerdoodle Collagen Fuel)
1/4 cup ghee, melted
1 tsp. salt

For the nut crumble topping:
1 cup pecans, chopped
1 cup walnuts, chopped
1/4 cup coconut sugar
1 scoop Primal Kitchen Collagen Fuel (Vanilla or Snickerdoodle)
1/4 cup almond flour
1/4 cup Primal Kitchen Avocado Oil
1/2 tsp. salt

Recipe: https://www.primalkitchen.com/blogs/recipes/sweet-potato-casserole
.

Which Primal Kitchen dressing would you pair with this California Chicken Salad? Let us know below.👇 

#repost: @weeknightbite - 🥗COPYCAT CALIFORNIA CHICKEN SALAD🥗 - serves 4.
4 cups or large handfuls chopped romaine
1 cup broccoli florets, chopped into bite-sized pieces
3/4 cup cherry tomatoes, halved
1/3 cup shredded carrots
Handful of SimpleMills Veggie Pita Crackers (or other pita chips)
3 tbsp crumbled feta cheese
1-2 breasts of an organic rotisserie chicken, shredded
1/2 cup cooked lentil pasta (I used tolerantfoods lentil rotini)
1 avocado, sliced
3-4 tbsp your favorite balsamic vinaigrette (I used @PrimalKitchenfoods)
Salt & pepper to taste

1. Place romaine in a large, shallow salad bowl. Tip: using a shallow bowl means you won't lose all the yummy toppings at the bottom of the bowl!
2. Top with all other ingredients. Pour dressing over the top, then toss everything together. 
3. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Enjoy!

#PrimalKitchen #EatLikeYourLifeDependsOnIt

Consider our Spicy Chicken Buffalo Sandwich our battle cry in the chicken sandwich wars of 2021. 🤤 #FlippingDelicious 

Ingredients:
2 1/2 ounces pork rinds (We used Epic brand)
1/3 cup melted butter or ghee
4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts cut into tenders
1 tsp. water
4 Tbsp. Primal Kitchen Mayo with Avocado Oil
1 cup Primal Kitchen Buffalo Sauce
4 Unbun Grain-Free Buns 
4 large pieces of iceberg lettuce
16 small pickle slices

#backthathassup to our bio link for all the juicy recipe details. #PrimalKitchen #EatLikeYourLifeDependsOnIt #ChickenSandwichWars
